Key findings:

The core event chain is consistent in code and runtime for the happy path: `bag.AddItem -> item.added -> task progress -> task.completed -> achievement.unlocked -> mail sent`, plus `item.added -> equipment auto-equip -> equip.success -> achievement`. That part behaved as expected when adding `2001` and `2002`.

The main defects are broken reward delivery and validation gaps. `claimreward` is effectively a dead-end because `signin.reward` has no consumer. `claimmail` is also a dead-end because `mail.claimed` has no consumer, so mail attachments never reach the bag. On top of that, `ClaimReward` is repeatable, `collector_100` is keyed off unlocked-achievement count rather than collected items, and direct `equip` allows fake item IDs to unlock `fully_equipped`. Together, these indicate the server has correct event wiring for some flows, but reward/ownership enforcement is incomplete and can produce false progression.
